[[File:Vulpes vulpes laying in snow.jpg|thumb|250px|{{lang|ja|狐}} (''kitsune''): a '''[[fox]]''' napping in the snow.]]
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|きつね}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=きつね|-}}. Appears in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.

Ultimate derivation {{unk|sort=きつね|nocap=1|ja}}. There are various theories. The most likely is based on the root form ''kitsu'', which may have originally been [[onomatopoeic]] for the sound of a fox's cry.<ref>'''1937''': ''Daigenkai'' (in Japanese). Reissued in 1984. {{ISBN|4-572-00062-X}}</ref> The final ''ne'' syllable appeared for certain by the {{w|Heian period}},<ref name="sasama">'''1998''': {{lang|ja|『怪異・きつね百物語』}} (''Yōkai: Kitsune Hyaku Monogatari'', “Phantoms: 100 Fox Tales”; in Japanese). Yoshihiko Sasama. {{ISBN|4-639-01544-5}}</ref> but its meaning remains unclear.

